						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the shrine of the goddess in the Nāgēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟañjaḍaiyaṉ: year 4+4</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription is dated in the 4th year opposite to the fourth year of the Pāṇḍya king Māṟañjaḍaiyaṉ and records the gift of 138 cows by the king for the supply of milk and ghee to the temple of Bhaṭāra of Tirukkīḻk-kōṭṭam in Tirukkuḍamukku <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Kumbakōṇam. It also records a gift of 100 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for burning two perpetual lamps in the same temple.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIV, No. 8.</p>						

						</summary>
